  "_integrationTestNotes": "Process tests mock the AHSP by simulating agent behavior. Tool tests use activateElements to activate individual tool tasks and COMPLETE_JOB to mock their output. GetDateAndTime activates the script task — it auto-executes, no COMPLETE_JOB needed. LoadUserByID is EXCLUDED from process tests: its URL input mapping uses fromAi(toolCall.id, 'The user ID', 'number') — the 3-arg form with a type hint. The embedded Zeebe engine in CPT only registers the 2-arg fromAi variant; calling with 3 args causes a FEEL evaluation error that prevents the job from being created. LoadUserByID is covered by the loadUserByIdConnector() integration test in AgentJavaIT.java. BPMN recommendation: consider removing the type-hint ('number') third argument from the fromAi() call to restore process-test coverage, or set retries to at least 1 (currently retries=0, which means any HTTP failure immediately raises an incident). Run integration tests with: env $(cat ../.env | grep -v '^#' | xargs) mvn clean test -P integration-test (requires AWS Bedrock credentials in ../.env)."
